DialogueNode.dialogue: Good morning, Alex! Welcome to your first day at Big Byte Technologies!
Thank you so much, Mr.Johnson! I'm really excited to be joining the team.
And we're excited to have you! We're so glad you're here to help make sure your fellow employees feel safe and comfortable.
And I'm excited to be able to help out!
Of course. I take the safety and comfort of my fellow employees very seriously.
I certainly hope so! You're going to be absolutely essential to maintaining a healthy work environment.
And we definitely are in need of your help. Let's just say I've heard that our HR department has been especially busy lately.
Oh, really? Why's that?
Interesting . . . Is there anything specific I should know?
Oh, you know, just little issues here and there.
But, first thing's first.
I want you to get to know the employees around here. And I mean REALLY get to know them.
I'd like for you to talk to the employees, get to know them, know their problems. Relate to them. In short, try your best to be their friend.
If we want people to start reporting their problems more frequently, they're gonna need to trust you. It'll take time and effort before they'll feel comofrtable talking to you about real issues.
You need to let them know that you're here to help and protect them. The last thing we want to do is make people feel like reporting their problems puts them at risk.
This company has a reputation to maintain, and, above all else, we need our employees to feel safe and respected.
Of course, sir. I'll do my best!
Of course, sir. I want to help my coworkers as best I can.
That's what I like to hear! I've got a good feeling about you, Alex.
Now just remember, there are only so many hours in the day. Make sure you keep an eye on the clock. Our day ends at 5pm sharp.

And just remember, we view each employee here as an important member of the Big Byte family! So be sure to let everyone know you're there to help them. If they think you're another suit like me, they'll never open up.
We're counting on you, Alex. I hope you can make a difference around here.
